  "text": "Lin neg marrow cells were stained for SKL, SLAM, or CD34, and each of the 4 EP receptors, and surface receptor expression on KL, SKL, SLAM SKL, and CD34 neg SKL cells was determined by FACS. For human EP receptors, UCB CD34 ϩ cells were positively selected with MACS microbeads [CITATION_1] and stained for CD34 and CD38 and each of the EP receptors, and surface receptor expression was determined by FACS. To evaluate CXCR4, Survivin, and active caspase-3, Lin neg cells or CD34 ϩ UCB was treated on ice with either 1 M dmPGE 2 or vehicle control for 2 hours, washed, and then cultured in RPMI-1640/10% HI-FBS at 37°C for 24 hours, stained for SKL (murine cells) and CXCR4, Survivin, and/or active caspase-3 as described earlier, and analyzed by FACS.",
